Distribution. Turkey , Rhodos, Greece (Thracia) (
Harz, 1969
); Anatolia (
Ramme, 1951
); the southern Balkans and Asia Minor (
Heller, 1988
); Greece : Thrace (
Kaltenbach, 1965
;
Willemse, 1984
,
Willemse & Willemse, 2008
;
Kati & Willemse, 2001
). Known in Turkey from Ïzmir, Manisa, Bursa provinces (
Werner, 1901
;
Uvarov, 1934
;
Ramme, 1951
;
Karabaġ, 1958
); it is recorded from Kütahya, Burdur, Denizli provinces for the first time in the present work (
Fig. 156
).

Remarks. The type is lost (
Harz, 1969
). Therefore a male neotype is designated from its known type locality Ïzmir: Buca.

The record given as 

B. dilatatus

from Ïzmir (

Ramme, 
1951

) probably belongs to this species.
